Program: Free Thinking
Title: Dramatising Democracy: Michael Dobbs, James Graham, Paula Milne, Trudi-Ann Tierney
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04yb7k6
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 20 Jan 2015
Author Michael Dobbs, dramatists James Graham and Paula Milne and TV producer Trudi-Ann Tierney join Anne McElvoy in the BBC Radio Theatre as part of BBC Democracy Day. They debate whether dramas like The West Wing, Borgen or This House aid our understanding of the way governments operate or do they foster cynicism about democracy? Producer: Harry Parker. Show less